15:47.166 --> 15:49.542
Please do not wear that.

15:52.959 --> 15:55.081
Let's just be honest, Auntie.

15:55.083 --> 15:56.458
- You don't think
- that I'm beautiful.

15:56.462 --> 15:58.166
- Sure, you have
- all the nice platitudes...

15:58.170 --> 16:00.083
- Vocabulary word from
- the 6th grade, might I add...

16:00.086 --> 16:01.126
- Niecy...

16:01.127 --> 16:02.165
- No, no, no, no, no.

16:02.166 --> 16:03.563
You don't think I'm beautiful.

16:03.564 --> 16:04.957
You don't think I'm smart.

16:04.959 --> 16:06.064
You think I'm just some...

16:06.065 --> 16:07.165
I don't know.

16:07.166 --> 16:09.874
Hey, hardheaded girl.

16:09.875 --> 16:10.876
I'm trying

16:10.877 --> 16:11.875
to apologize to you.

16:11.877 --> 16:13.749
[chuckles]

16:13.750 --> 16:15.793
You know, although not

16:15.794 --> 16:17.832
the ideal circumstances,

16:17.834 --> 16:20.083
- I thought that living with you
- was gonna be fun,

16:20.086 --> 16:22.083
Full of girls' night in

16:22.084 --> 16:24.081
and movie nights

16:24.083 --> 16:26.665
and late-night talks,

16:26.667 --> 16:27.749
me being inspired by you.

16:27.750 --> 16:29.332
But what I got was freedom.

16:29.333 --> 16:31.542
- That night
- I was free from your judgment,

16:31.545 --> 16:33.521
My worst fear happened,

16:33.522 --> 16:35.498
and I'm still here.

16:35.500 --> 16:37.000
I didn't implode

16:37.001 --> 16:38.498
from your ridicule.

16:38.500 --> 16:41.415
Auntie, I love you. I do.

16:41.417 --> 16:43.250
But I don't really need

16:43.251 --> 16:45.081
an apology from you,

16:45.083 --> 16:46.188
because I no longer care

16:46.189 --> 16:47.291
what you think.

16:50.750 --> 16:54.540
I hear you,

16:54.542 --> 16:56.085
and all I can do

16:56.086 --> 16:57.624
is say that I'm sorry

16:57.625 --> 17:01.291
and I'll do better.

17:04.625 --> 17:06.666
[door shuts]

17:09.290 --> 17:10.709
- (Kara)
- Those are competitive numbers,

17:10.712 --> 17:12.396
So that means

17:12.396 --> 17:14.080
that I need to hear

17:14.083 --> 17:15.334
some great pitches

17:15.335 --> 17:16.582
on the issues that matter

17:16.583 --> 17:17.752
surrounding this election,

17:17.752 --> 17:18.915
all right?

17:18.916 --> 17:23.415
For example, education.

17:23.416 --> 17:25.080
Minimum wage.

17:25.083 --> 17:26.855
- Um, gun control.

17:26.856 --> 17:28.624
- Yup.

17:28.625 --> 17:31.665
"Who's voting now" stories.

17:31.667 --> 17:33.084
All right? The point is,

17:33.085 --> 17:34.498
let's get creative.

17:34.500 --> 17:36.583
Let's think outside the box.

17:39.291 --> 17:41.083
Um...

17:43.583 --> 17:44.834
Same-sex will always be

17:44.835 --> 17:46.083
a hot issue.

17:59.375 --> 18:01.540
Excuse me.

18:01.542 --> 18:02.874
What was that?

18:02.875 --> 18:04.207
What did I do now?

18:04.208 --> 18:05.397
We just keep

18:05.398 --> 18:06.582
doing the same thing

18:06.583 --> 18:08.707
over and over and over again,

18:08.709 --> 18:09.709
and it's not

18:09.710 --> 18:10.708
what we set out to do,

18:10.710 --> 18:12.916
and I can't do it anymore.

18:12.917 --> 18:16.083
What? You can't do your job?

18:21.083 --> 18:22.667
Is your life so good that you

18:22.668 --> 18:24.248
can't do what's expected of you

18:24.250 --> 18:25.501
because it's too much

18:25.502 --> 18:26.749
of a burden?

18:26.750 --> 18:28.498
Please. Kill the melodrama.

18:28.500 --> 18:29.665
Really?

18:29.667 --> 18:31.165
We could be doing better,

18:31.166 --> 18:32.334
but we're just doing

18:32.335 --> 18:33.498
what everyone else is doing.

18:33.500 --> 18:34.792
Talk Back was supposed

18:34.793 --> 18:36.081
to be different, remember?

18:36.083 --> 18:38.125
- Talk Back was supposed to have
- a different perspective,

18:38.128 --> 18:39.334
One that nobody else

18:39.335 --> 18:40.540
was thinking about

18:40.542 --> 18:42.001
or dared to even consider,

18:42.002 --> 18:43.457
let alone air.

18:43.458 --> 18:45.063
Mary Jane, you know that

18:45.064 --> 18:46.665
we've always had to give them

18:46.667 --> 18:48.834
- a little bit of what they want
- to get what we want.

18:48.837 --> 18:50.792
- Except I never got
- what I wanted.

18:50.795 --> 18:52.081
What are you talking about?

18:52.083 --> 18:53.251
You just went rogue

18:53.252 --> 18:54.415
on a suicide piece.

18:54.417 --> 18:56.064
And I also did the modern-day

18:56.065 --> 18:57.707
motherhood story

18:57.709 --> 18:59.396
that got me a focus group

18:59.397 --> 19:01.081
that said I was too arrogant.

19:01.083 --> 19:02.625
- Those two things
- are not connected.

19:02.629 --> 19:04.373
Results are still the same.

19:04.375 --> 19:06.373
Okay.

19:06.375 --> 19:08.208
- You want me to say
- I was wrong about the story?

19:08.212 --> 19:09.624
No.

19:09.625 --> 19:11.081
I was wrong.

19:11.083 --> 19:12.147
If the focus groups

19:12.148 --> 19:13.207
are gonna take me down,

19:13.208 --> 19:15.146
I want to go down

19:15.147 --> 19:17.081
on my own terms, okay?

19:17.083 --> 19:18.332
I've been a good team player,

19:18.333 --> 19:20.582
and where has that gotten me?

19:20.583 --> 19:23.250
- I've given up too much of what
- I want in the Talk Back segment,

19:23.253 --> 19:25.208
- But I've... I've finally
- figured out what direction

19:25.212 --> 19:26.332
I want to take the show.

19:26.333 --> 19:28.397
Great.

19:28.398 --> 19:30.457
Then say it in the meeting.

19:30.458 --> 19:31.959
I was wrong about that.

19:31.960 --> 19:33.457
I'm sorry.

19:33.458 --> 19:34.938
Look, Kara, we are still gonna

19:34.939 --> 19:36.415
be hitting them hard

19:36.417 --> 19:38.248
on our new stories, okay?

19:38.250 --> 19:39.459
We're still gonna be

19:39.460 --> 19:40.665
cultivating new pundits

19:40.667 --> 19:43.290
and... and field reporters.

19:43.291 --> 19:45.332
But the Talk Back segment?

19:45.333 --> 19:47.501
It's got to be stories

19:47.502 --> 19:49.665
that... that matter to me most:

19:49.667 --> 19:50.959
the black community,

19:50.960 --> 19:52.248
black women,

19:52.250 --> 19:54.834
- and shedding light on stories
- that don't get enough attention.

19:54.837 --> 19:56.916
Wait. All black stories?

19:56.917 --> 19:59.248
Yeah, all black everything.

19:59.250 --> 20:00.647
Are you trying to do the news

20:00.648 --> 20:02.040
or build your brand?

20:02.041 --> 20:03.209
'Cause that's

20:03.210 --> 20:04.373
what it sounds like.

20:04.375 --> 20:06.123
Maybe I am.

20:06.125 --> 20:07.916
Oh.

20:07.917 --> 20:09.772
I am tired

20:09.773 --> 20:11.624
of giving my all to something

20:11.625 --> 20:12.625
and winding up with nothing.

20:12.627 --> 20:14.998
So we're talking about...

20:15.000 --> 20:16.208
- [laughs]
- Never mind.

20:16.210 --> 20:17.124
No, no, no, say it.

20:17.126 --> 20:20.208
No. I'll take it to Greg.

20:21.709 --> 20:23.542
Thank you.

